query: What is the role of Kingstown in the geography of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines?
summary: Kingstown is very important in geography of Saint Vincent and Grenadines because it is capital city of country. It is the number one city on St. Vincent Island, which is main island in St. Vincent Group and also biggest island for area (342.7 km²) and people (109,000). Kingstown is center for doing administration and business, and it connects smaller towns in St. Vincent Group like Georgetown, Byera Village, Biabou, and Chateaubelair. More, because it is capital city, Kingstown is very important place that connects St. Vincent Group with other islands in north part of Grenadines.
